review_data.content: For the lunch delivery, it was not a bad option. I liked the idea of adding watermelon on top of the noodles, although the noodles were a bit salty. Sushi was also not bad in comparison to other sushi restaurants in Zurich, although the amount of rice per nigiri was a bit large.

Great food, great ambiance. The prices are on the steeper side though.
The outdoor seating is very comfortable.
The menu contains a lot of options. The Sushi is fresh, has awesome flavours and there are different types.
There were also some great beverage options.
The noodle soup bowls are recommended... Are fresh and flavorful.

Booked Order 30-Dec for New Year’s Eve - it was cancelled 15 min prior pick up time! We got to know about it only when we got to Nooch. The service guy did not even apologize- he just said - I cancelled your order 20:45/15min ago - here is the email… this is beyond bad - I have no words - there is no way I can ever count on/trust this place again !!! (It of course adds a bit more to the unpleasant experience this happening on New Years Eve when most places are closed for the evening… )
It used to be my favorite place for sushi - never setting a foot here again.

P.s. I wished the service guy a nice start of the New Year - he did not get my irony ;)
